page.title: 01The Ousden area
page.content: The largest part of this block is the village of Ousden, with small parts of the parishes of Lidgate, Hargrabe, Dalham and Wickhambrook in the county of Suffolk. The whole area is farmed, mainly grain, with just a few animals. The village of Ousden has a population of about 200, and is quite small with the majority of houses being of ribbon development on or near Ousden Hill to the 'Fox' public house, then turning left from the Fow down Dunstall Green Road. There is just one block of houses named Rockall and this is owned by the council. The countryside is very open and for Suffolk quite high. The Fox is in fact the highest pub in the country at 400ft above sea level.
